Yes, the code will compile, but it depends on the type of exception being declared.
In Java, method overriding follows strict rules for exceptions:
A subclass method cannot throw broader (more general) checked exceptions than the superclass method.
However, it can throw the same, narrower, or no checked exceptions.
For unchecked exceptions (RuntimeException), there are no such restrictions.
🔹 Given Scenario
