HashMap allows one null key and multiple null values, while ConcurrentHashMap does not allow nulls (to avoid ambiguity in 
concurrent reads).
ConcurrentHashMap provides better scalability and performance in multi-threaded environments.
👉 Conclusion: Use HashMap in single-threaded scenarios and ConcurrentHashMap for high-performance, thread-safe operations in
concurrent systems.

